WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:02.903
EVERYBODY HATES CHRIS #025
"Everybody Hates Elections"
CLOSED CAPTIONED

00:02.936 --> 00:04.172
CHRIS ROCK:
I thought running
for class president

00:04.205 --> 00:07.375
would make me more popular,
change my life at Corleone,

00:07.408 --> 00:08.609
but the more I campaigned,

00:08.642 --> 00:10.611
the more I just wanted
to beat Caruso

00:10.644 --> 00:12.646
by any means necessary.

00:12.680 --> 00:14.482
Dude, I've got bad news.

00:14.515 --> 00:16.350
The entire fourth period
English class

00:16.384 --> 00:17.551
is going to vote
for Caruso.

00:17.585 --> 00:19.553
All of 'em?

00:19.587 --> 00:21.255
Yeah. He said if they don't
vote for him,

00:21.289 --> 00:22.356
he was going to kick the lit
out of them.

00:22.390 --> 00:24.625
I thought having DiPaolo run
with me would help me.

00:24.658 --> 00:26.627
It would probably help more
if he threatened

00:26.660 --> 00:28.196
to knock somebody's teeth out.

00:28.229 --> 00:29.530
That's okay.
He won't be able

00:29.563 --> 00:31.299
to do that
at the town hall meeting.

00:31.332 --> 00:33.201
I may not be able to knock
people out,

00:33.234 --> 00:34.735
but I know I can answer
some questions.

00:34.768 --> 00:37.071
(Duran Duran's
"Notorious" playing)

00:37.105 --> 00:38.606
Take a look at this.

00:38.639 --> 00:40.574
I think it'll help
with the swing vote.

00:40.608 --> 00:42.243
"Swing vote" meant
"white vote."

00:42.276 --> 00:44.545
What's that?

00:44.578 --> 00:46.647
I redid your posters.

00:46.680 --> 00:47.681
We need to take advantage

00:47.715 --> 00:49.183
of DiPaolo
being your running mate.

00:49.217 --> 00:52.386
Uh, well, where's my name?

00:52.420 --> 00:55.189
Down here.
I'd get votes if they didn't
read the fine print.

00:55.223 --> 00:56.390
I'm the one running
for president.

00:56.424 --> 00:58.592
I think my name should be
a little bit bigger than that.

00:58.626 --> 00:59.727
I have another one.

01:02.663 --> 01:04.632
White people at the beach?

01:04.665 --> 01:08.202
No, happy white people
at the beach.

01:08.236 --> 01:09.637
Chris...

01:09.670 --> 01:12.373
Oh, that's great!

01:13.407 --> 01:14.375
Where's your picture?

01:14.408 --> 01:15.609
Next to Waldo.

01:15.643 --> 01:16.677
Still working on that.

01:16.710 --> 01:18.279
I was thinking...

01:18.312 --> 01:19.647
We should
have another opportunity

01:19.680 --> 01:20.481
to hear our candidates

01:20.514 --> 01:22.716
in addition
to the town hall meeting.

01:22.750 --> 01:25.319
So you're going to
have to prepare a speech.

01:25.353 --> 01:26.187
A speech?

01:26.220 --> 01:27.588
I never feared speaking
in public

01:27.621 --> 01:29.690
until I had to speak in public.

01:30.724 --> 01:32.460
No problem, Ms. Morello.

01:32.493 --> 01:33.861
Okay.

01:33.894 --> 01:35.329
No problem?

01:35.363 --> 01:37.831
You ever written
a speech before? I haven't.

01:37.865 --> 01:39.500
Oh, by the way,

01:39.533 --> 01:41.469
are you going to need
an organ player?

01:41.502 --> 01:43.737
Why would I need
an organ player?

01:43.771 --> 01:47.608
Oh, you know, in case
you catch the Holy Ghost.

01:47.641 --> 01:50.244
Uh, no, I think
I'll be okay.

01:50.278 --> 01:51.412
Tambourine?

01:51.445 --> 01:52.546
CHRIS:
I'm fine.

01:52.580 --> 01:53.881
Good luck.

01:53.914 --> 01:58.586
Didn't Ghostbusters already
catch the Holy Ghost?

02:06.660 --> 02:08.562
* Oh... make it funky now.

